description:
Final pass: This was missed because reviewers focused on the error paths, not the flow from ipv6_len assignment to use.

Root cause: At line 1588:
  ipv6_len = sizeof(rx_ipv6_buf);  // Set to buffer size
  ret = peer_try_all_pubkeys(..., &ipv6_len, ...);

If peer_try_all_pubkeys succeeds, ipv6_len is modified by lichen_link_rx() to contain the actual decompressed packet length. This is correct.

However, the code at line 1599-1604:
  if (ipv6_len > sizeof(rx_ipv6_buf)) {
      LOG_ERR(...);
      ...
      return;
  }

This check happens AFTER peer_try_all_pubkeys returns. If peer_try_all_pubkeys (via lichen_link_rx) wrote more than rx_ipv6_buf holds, the buffer overflow has ALREADY occurred - this check only detects it after the fact.

WAIT - re-reading line 1588, ipv6_len = sizeof(rx_ipv6_buf) is the INPUT size telling lichen_link_rx the buffer capacity. lichen_link_rx should validate this internally. The post-check is defense in depth against a buggy lichen_link_rx.

This is by design - ipv6_len is an in-out parameter. Not a bug.
